explanation: This solution uses a single pass through the string to count the number of substrings with equal number of consecutive 1's and 0's. It keeps track of the length of the current sequence of consecutive characters and increments the count whenever it encounters a different character. The minimum of the current sequence length and 1 is added to the count to account for the current sequence and any remaining sequences.

